This is going well.
Look how happy she looks.

666
00:46:21,653 --> 00:46:26,010
l wish we could afford a pad in the Hamptons.
Everybody who's anybody has one.

667
00:46:26,093 --> 00:46:31,213
But if you're somebody who's nobody, it's no
fun to be around anybody who's everybody.

668
00:46:31,293 --> 00:46:34,205
lsn't he charming?
And don't tell me he's not gorgeous.

669
00:46:34,293 --> 00:46:36,523
lf you like perfect features.

670
00:46:36,613 --> 00:46:38,683
Don't be such a crab.

671
00:46:38,773 --> 00:46:41,845
l'm gonna try to come out here more often.

672
00:46:42,813 --> 00:46:45,486
- Wow, it's so big.
- Thank you.

673
00:46:45,573 --> 00:46:49,566
lt's so clean, too.
lt's a great place to entertain, which l love.

674
00:46:49,653 --> 00:46:52,850
- God, Hobie, isn't it amazing?
- Yeah, l love the ramp.

675
00:46:52,933 --> 00:46:56,130
lt's wheelchair accessible.
That's important out here.

676
00:46:56,213 --> 00:46:58,886
- Go ahead, guys. Go in.
- Thanks.

677
00:47:02,333 --> 00:47:06,326
lt's tremendous for aerobics.
Come on, try it, Hobie.

678
00:47:06,413 --> 00:47:08,369
What do you do for exercise?

679
00:47:08,453 --> 00:47:11,843
Tiddlywinks.
And an occasional anxiety attack.

680
00:47:11,933 --> 00:47:16,404
- Try it, Hobie. lt's good manners.
- Since when do l have good manners?

681
00:47:16,493 --> 00:47:19,803
- What is that? ls it a pig?
- l don't know.

682
00:47:19,893 --> 00:47:22,123
Hey, Greg, did you shoot this?

683
00:47:22,213 --> 00:47:24,773
Well, actually, l shot all of those.

684
00:47:24,853 --> 00:47:28,926
Twice a year l go to Africa.
The experience would take your breath away.

685
00:47:29,013 --> 00:47:32,005
Huge herds of kudu -
greater kudu and lesser kudu.

686
00:47:32,093 --> 00:47:35,369
- Which is bigger? The greater or the lesser?
- Hobie!

687
00:47:35,453 --> 00:47:41,528
l think it would be the sexiest thing to sleep
under the stars in the middle of the jungle...

688
00:47:41,613 --> 00:47:45,128
lf you don't mind waking up
with a python in your sleeping bag.

689
00:47:45,213 --> 00:47:49,729
No, no. The whole thing is very civilised.
They have beds and bathrooms and showers.

690
00:47:49,813 --> 00:47:54,603
But no elevators. ln case you're being chased
by a tiger and you have to get up into a tree.

691
00:47:54,693 --> 00:47:57,685
- l'd have to take the elevator.
- l don't understand.

692
00:47:57,773 --> 00:48:00,287
- Me neither.
- Did you shoot all the furniture?

693
00:48:00,373 --> 00:48:05,083
- So, Melinda, have you ever shot a gun?
- How quickly was it shot? Freshly shot?

694
00:48:10,093 --> 00:48:12,926
- Right here?
- That's fine. This was fun. Thank you.

695
00:48:13,013 --> 00:48:15,652
- Are you sure you'll be all right?
- l'm fine.

696
00:48:15,733 --> 00:48:19,646
- Do you wanna come up for a drink?
- A drink! Yeah, we could do that.

697
00:48:19,733 --> 00:48:22,850
- We can't. You have to get up early.
- Why? l'm out of work.

698
00:48:22,933 --> 00:48:26,721
Hey, do you have any tequila?
l make the world's most potent margarita.

699
00:48:26,813 --> 00:48:28,849
- They're very strong.
- l sure do.

700
00:48:28,933 --> 00:48:31,493
- Are you all right?
- Here, can l help you?

701
00:48:31,573 --> 00:48:34,883
- Very good. You know this car so well.
- He's like an old man.

702
00:48:34,973 --> 00:48:38,045
- Thank you.
- l'm fine.

703
00:48:38,133 --> 00:48:39,725
lt's like we're dancing.

704
00:48:39,813 --> 00:48:42,964
- Tequila's on the surgeon general's list.
- Just be quiet.

705
00:48:43,053 --> 00:48:46,090
Why'd he stop twice to get the car washed?

706
00:48:46,613 --> 00:48:50,891
God, he's incredible, isn't he?
lt'd be great for Melinda if things worked out.

707
00:48:50,973 --> 00:48:53,407
l wouldn't let that guy fill my teeth.

708
00:48:53,493 --> 00:48:56,929
l mean, anyone who gets his jollies
putting holes in animals...

709
00:48:57,013 --> 00:48:59,846
The Ernest Hemingway of the root canal set.

710
00:48:59,933 --> 00:49:02,652
He's probably got her in bed by now.

711
00:49:03,453 --> 00:49:06,013
l didn't think she could stand him.

712
00:49:06,093 --> 00:49:08,971
Not every woman falls
for that phoney social rap,

713
00:49:09,053 --> 00:49:14,923
you know, with the Haut-Brion and
special cheeses and backgammon trophy.

714
00:49:15,013 --> 00:49:17,322
Someone must blow him up with an air hose.

715
00:49:17,413 --> 00:49:22,646
You know what? Can we just not discuss it?
And, frankly, l thought you acted like a clown.

716
00:49:22,733 --> 00:49:26,123
Now, can l talk to you for a minute?
And try not to get upset.

717
00:49:26,213 --> 00:49:30,729
What? You wanna spend more time in
the Hamptons whether l go with you or not?

718
00:49:30,813 --> 00:49:33,646
l told you Steve Walsh
is gonna co-produce my film.

719
00:49:33,733 --> 00:49:38,011
Yes, that's fantastic. l figured out
a great way to play the psychiatrist.

720
00:49:38,093 --> 00:49:41,244
lt's fresh. With a limp. l do a great limp,

721
00:49:41,333 --> 00:49:44,211
and that will account
for his crushing insecurity.

722
00:49:44,293 --> 00:49:47,649
That way, when l make a pass at Rosalie,
l expect the rejection.

723
00:49:47,733 --> 00:49:49,928
You won't be able to play the shrink.

724
00:49:50,013 --> 00:49:52,243
- Why not?
- Steve wants a name.

725
00:49:52,333 --> 00:49:55,803
- l have a name on my driver's licence.
- He won't go with an unknown.

726
00:49:55,893 --> 00:49:59,647
- You're the director. You say what goes.
- Without him, there's no film.

727
00:49:59,733 --> 00:50:02,645
But l'm the perfect psychiatrist. You said it.

728
00:50:02,733 --> 00:50:05,725
l think l can find something else
for you in the script.

729
00:50:05,813 --> 00:50:08,088
- Like what?
- What about Moe Flanders?

730
00:50:08,173 --> 00:50:11,688
You'd be a natural.
You're more Flanders than you are the shrink.

731
00:50:11,773 --> 00:50:16,767
Flanders? The retarded elevator operator
with the cleft palate?

732
00:50:16,853 --> 00:50:20,892
- ls that how you see me?
- When have l said you had a cleft palate?

733
00:50:20,973 --> 00:50:23,931
- Help!
- My God. That's Melinda.

734
00:50:24,013 --> 00:50:27,130
He's raping her.
Probably put Novocaine in her margarita.

735
00:50:27,213 --> 00:50:30,808
- Help! Help!
- What is it? What's wrong? What's wrong?

736
00:50:30,893 --> 00:50:33,885
l got a tick! There's a tick in my leg.

737
00:50:33,973 --> 00:50:37,682
- Where's Greg?
- He's a dentist. He doesn't do tick extractions.

738
00:50:37,773 --> 00:50:40,526
His beeper went off.
He had some kind of emergency.

739
00:50:40,613 --> 00:50:43,525
Someone saw a rhino on Sixth Avenue
and they needed a hunter.

740
00:50:43,613 --> 00:50:47,401
- Get it out! Quick! Please! Please!
- l don't know how. ln the Bronx we had mice.

741
00:50:47,493 --> 00:50:51,805
You need a doctor. You can't pull it out cos
the body comes out and the head stays in.

742
00:50:51,893 --> 00:50:55,806
- l feel terrible. l think l'm gonna faint.
- Take her to the emergency room.

743
00:50:55,893 --> 00:50:59,886
- There's a tick inside me sucking my blood!
- lt's not sucking your blood.

744
00:50:59,973 --> 00:51:03,010
Those are leeches.
But this is disgusting enough.

745
00:51:31,893 --> 00:51:35,886
l'm so sorry. lt was so nice of you
to come and hang with me.

746
00:51:35,973 --> 00:51:37,372
That's OK.

747
00:51:37,453 --> 00:51:43,323
Actually, l love watching a live creature being
pulled out of somebody's body at 3.30am.

748
00:51:43,413 --> 00:51:48,806
- lf that happens again, please call me.
- lt was really nice of you - this whole day.

749
00:51:48,893 --> 00:51:51,566
lt's obvious
you don't care much for the beach.

750
00:51:51,653 --> 00:51:57,523
lt's not the beach so much as the ocean, the
sand and the seagulls and things like that.

751
00:51:57,613 --> 00:51:59,410
Well, go.

752
00:51:59,493 --> 00:52:02,053
You've had a long day. Rest.

753
00:52:02,133 --> 00:52:05,205
Call me. l'm over here if you need me. OK?

754
00:52:05,293 --> 00:52:09,491
But try not to panic.
The screaming frightened me.

755
00:52:09,573 --> 00:52:14,442
And you would be totally cool if you had a
live insect crawling around under your skin?

756
00:52:14,533 --> 00:52:16,808
l wouldn't enjoy it, but l wouldn't panic.

757
00:52:16,893 --> 00:52:20,044
That's good because
there's one in the back of your neck.

758
00:52:20,133 --> 00:52:21,725
- My neck?
- Your neck.

759
00:52:21,813 --> 00:52:23,963
- My neck?
- Yes. Right here. lt's OK.

760
00:52:24,053 --> 00:52:26,283
- Get it off! Get it off me!
- Relax. OK.

761
00:52:31,013 --> 00:52:33,925
This is exciting.
l've never been to the races before.

762
00:52:34,013 --> 00:52:38,291
Here's a horse called Broadway Melody.
l think that's a lucky name.

763
00:52:38,373 --> 00:52:44,369
Well, it's not very sensible to pick horses
by their names, but l guess it's romantic.

764
00:52:57,413 --> 00:52:59,324
That was so beautiful.

765
00:52:59,413 --> 00:53:02,610
There is no more sublime music
than that second movement.

766
00:53:02,693 --> 00:53:05,924
Laurel cannot listen without crying.
Her eyes are all red.

767
00:53:06,013 --> 00:53:10,404
l'm with her. When Raphael first laid eyes
upon the Sistine Chapel he passed out.

768
00:53:10,493 --> 00:53:13,803
- Aren't you gonna find us a taxi?
- Yeah, let's go.

769
00:53:13,893 --> 00:53:16,248
She's head over heels in love with him.

770
00:53:16,333 --> 00:53:19,689
He's gifted, sensitive.
He is unfazed by the details of her past.

771
00:53:19,773 --> 00:53:22,446
He is, in fact, moved by her suffering.

772
00:53:22,533 --> 00:53:28,165
Even the awful story she's been
reluctant to tell but feels that she must.

773
00:53:28,813 --> 00:53:31,088
l killed him.

774
00:53:31,173 --> 00:53:33,767
But it was an accident.

775
00:53:35,093 --> 00:53:36,890
No.

776
00:53:38,573 --> 00:53:42,851
ln my defence, l will say
l was out of my mind on drugs.

777
00:53:42,933 --> 00:53:45,811
l shouldn't say drugs. Pills.

778
00:53:45,893 --> 00:53:48,726
Pills to help me sleep at night,
pills to keep me awake,

779
00:53:48,813 --> 00:53:55,252
whatever l could get my hands on to sweep
my various pains and anxieties under the rug.

780
00:53:57,573 --> 00:54:01,327
But if l'm honest about it, l did mean to do it.

781
00:54:01,413 --> 00:54:03,210
No.

782
00:54:05,333 --> 00:54:08,450
l denied it in the trial, of course.

783
00:54:08,533 --> 00:54:10,922
But the fact is, l...

784
00:54:12,493 --> 00:54:15,246
l couldn't think of what else to do.

785
00:54:16,053 --> 00:54:19,090
l thought about killing myself.

786
00:54:19,173 --> 00:54:23,371
Why l didn't, l can't say.
lt would have been much more rational.

787
00:54:23,453 --> 00:54:26,923
l thought about killing his girlfriend.

788
00:54:28,613 --> 00:54:30,763
Maryanne was her name.

789
00:54:30,853 --> 00:54:32,844
Maryanne Lane.

790
00:54:35,373 --> 00:54:37,568
And it was...

791
00:54:38,613 --> 00:54:41,002
lt was so easy buying a gun.

792
00:54:42,493 --> 00:54:47,487
l just drove out of state
and l walked into a store and l bought one.

793
00:54:47,573 --> 00:54:49,370
There were no questions asked.

794
00:54:49,453 --> 00:54:56,052
l bought a box of bullets and l loaded it
like l'd been handling one my whole life.

795
00:54:57,493 --> 00:55:00,724
lt was all very premeditated,

796
00:55:02,253 --> 00:55:06,883
despite what my attorneys
would have everyone believe.

797
00:55:06,973 --> 00:55:09,362
And then l

798
00:55:09,453 --> 00:55:11,808
drove back to where he worked.

799
00:55:11,893 --> 00:55:17,251
lt was next to a Christian Science
reading room. l remember that.

800
00:55:17,333 --> 00:55:21,246
And l just waited out the front
for him to come out.

801
00:55:21,333 --> 00:55:24,484
And even that wasn't very difficult.

802
00:55:25,293 --> 00:55:30,003
There was a slight drizzle, l remember that,
but the wait wasn't interminable.

803
00:55:30,093 --> 00:55:32,084
And then

804
00:55:33,173 --> 00:55:38,247
when he came out and walked to his car,
l simply confronted him.

805
00:55:39,053 --> 00:55:43,046
And he said some
very cold and cruel things to me,

806
00:55:43,133 --> 00:55:47,331
and l shot Mr San Giuliano

807
00:55:50,413 --> 00:55:52,608
as l had planned to.

808
00:55:54,813 --> 00:55:57,008
As l had planned.

809
00:56:01,691 --> 00:56:07,721
Well, they must have felt the circumstances
were extenuating if you got off so lightly.

810
00:56:07,811 --> 00:56:09,961
lt may seem lightly to you,

811
00:56:10,411 --> 00:56:12,402
but it was nothing but hell.

812
00:56:12,491 --> 00:56:18,088
And if you've never been arrested and put
on trial, well, that alone is sentence enough.

813
00:56:18,171 --> 00:56:20,446
The horror, the...

814
00:56:20,531 --> 00:56:26,925
the tension, the police, the journalists...
l went over my story hundreds of times -

815
00:56:27,011 --> 00:56:30,526
the jilted mother, seduced away
from her family, sick on drugs,

816
00:56:30,611 --> 00:56:34,081
the struggle for the gun, the gun goes off.

817
00:56:37,291 --> 00:56:39,680
But there was no struggle.

818
00:56:41,451 --> 00:56:43,760
That was legal fiction.

819
00:56:44,611 --> 00:56:47,489
Well, you had good lawyers.

820
00:56:47,571 --> 00:56:50,039
Not like your child custody team.

821
00:56:53,971 --> 00:56:58,601
l rememberjust lying
in my cell at night and thinking,

822
00:56:59,411 --> 00:57:01,402
''My God.''

823
00:57:03,331 --> 00:57:06,926
''You are Melinda Nash from Park Avenue.''

824
00:57:08,771 --> 00:57:13,640
''What the hell are you doing
in a women's prison in lllinois?''

825
00:57:15,971 --> 00:57:21,170
So, naturally, after l got out
l decided to end it all.

826
00:57:26,011 --> 00:57:28,081
What do you want?

827
00:57:32,571 --> 00:57:37,565
l want to want to live.

828
00:57:39,051 --> 00:57:41,246
Everybody wants to live.

829
00:57:47,451 --> 00:57:51,603
Now that l met you,
l'm feeling a little more positive about it.

830
00:57:52,571 --> 00:57:55,563
Congratulate me. l just got canned.

831
00:57:57,011 --> 00:58:01,562
My version differs from theirs. They would
have you believe l couldn't hold my liquor,

832
00:58:01,651 --> 00:58:05,246
which anyone who knows me
knows is a baseless canard.

833
00:58:05,331 --> 00:58:07,891
Lee, l knew this would happen.

834
00:58:08,611 --> 00:58:11,648
You did? Well, why didn't you tell me?

835
00:58:11,731 --> 00:58:14,928
l'm angry and disgusted.
l mean, Christ, can you blame them?

836
00:58:15,011 --> 00:58:19,562
Thank you for the emotional support.
l'll see you around.

837
00:58:24,091 --> 00:58:26,207
- Hey.
- Hi.

838
00:58:26,291 --> 00:58:30,762
- You all right? You seem a little glum.
- Lee got fired.

839
00:58:32,331 --> 00:58:33,810
What happened?

840
00:58:33,891 --> 00:58:36,485
lt was the producer.
They'd always wanted a name.

841
00:58:36,571 --> 00:58:40,200
- They got nervous cos ticket sales were slow.
- l'm sorry.

842
00:58:40,291 --> 00:58:44,250
- l know the realities of the marketplace.
- Yeah. So, what are you gonna do?

843
00:58:44,331 --> 00:58:48,643
l don't know if l should feel sorry for myself
or shop to blot out my depression.

844
00:58:48,731 --> 00:58:50,528
- Neither. Come with us.
- With you?

845
00:58:50,611 --> 00:58:54,286
Sure. l'm taking Melinda
to a recording session. Bartk.

846
00:58:54,371 --> 00:58:56,441
- No...
- lt'll take your mind off things.

847
00:58:56,531 --> 00:59:00,490
- You love Bartk. They're doing a quartet.
- You remembered?

848
00:59:00,571 --> 00:59:03,608
- Come on.
- Do l have time to change?

849
00:59:03,691 --> 00:59:07,445
- You look fine. Look at me.
- l feel so grungy. l've been working all day.

850
00:59:07,531 --> 00:59:11,729
- All right, but hurry, then we'll get a coffee.
- OK.

851
00:59:35,331 --> 00:59:38,403
- lt's beautiful, isn't it?
- They're so good.

852
00:59:38,491 --> 00:59:43,326
l could never decide between the piano and
the cello. The result is l play them both badly.

853
00:59:43,411 --> 00:59:46,608
- And the viola.
- l heard you play the piano. You're good.

854
00:59:46,691 --> 00:59:47,726
- No.
- Yes.

855
00:59:47,811 --> 00:59:51,599
Full of feeling.
You have a lovely touch of the keys.

856
00:59:51,691 --> 00:59:55,047
l can see a person's soul
by their intonation on an instrument -

857
00:59:55,131 --> 00:59:58,487
- keyboard, horn or strings. l can. lt's a gift.
- You saw my soul?

858
00:59:58,571 --> 01:00:02,849
Right off the bat. That first party,
when you sat down next to me to play,

859
01:00:02,931 --> 01:00:07,209
the minute you touched the keys
the chord went through me like a knife.

860
01:00:07,291 --> 01:00:09,964
l don't dare ask you what you saw.

861
01:00:12,411 --> 01:00:15,005
lt's great.

862
01:00:15,091 --> 01:00:19,881
Although l find
the more turbulent parts a little scary.

863
01:00:23,931 --> 01:00:26,491
- He's still not home.
- Come to dinner with us.

864
01:00:26,571 --> 01:00:29,131
- No, l can't.
- Come on. lt's gonna be fun.

865
01:00:29,211 --> 01:00:34,888
We'll go down to this little bistro downtown
west. lt's very quiet, very dark, very French.

866
01:00:34,971 --> 01:00:40,284
- l haven't been to a dark bistro since college.
- You'll love it. l've fallen in love there.

867
01:00:40,611 --> 01:00:42,488
No more for me.

868
01:00:42,571 --> 01:00:45,404
- Melinda was the fast, advanced one.
- Come on.

869
01:00:45,491 --> 01:00:48,688
All the men were crazy for her.
They were drawn to her.

870
01:00:48,771 --> 01:00:50,887
Her unpredictability.

871
01:00:50,971 --> 01:00:53,280
No, Laurel was the star of our group.

872
01:00:53,371 --> 01:00:56,727
l remember how jealous everyone was
when you married Lee.

873
01:00:56,811 --> 01:01:00,008
Lee was the most attractive,
most charismatic actor.

874
01:01:00,091 --> 01:01:06,166
My God. You almost broke Cassie's heart,
not that she'd ever admit it.

875
01:01:06,251 --> 01:01:11,200
Forgive me. Am l being too open here?
lt's just l feel great.

876
01:01:11,291 --> 01:01:13,566
- What is this?
- lt's a Haut-Brion.

877
01:01:13,651 --> 01:01:17,087
My head is swimming. But it feels good.

878
01:01:17,171 --> 01:01:22,006
You were the first one in our group to sleep
with a man. You were so very sophisticated.

879
01:01:22,091 --> 01:01:26,562
- l admired it. l did.
- Yeah, well, it was probably true.

880
01:01:26,651 --> 01:01:32,442
- l had a deep hunger for physical intimacy.
- A hunger that could not be denied.

881
01:01:32,531 --> 01:01:36,160
Not once adolescence descended
and the hormones kicked in.

882
01:01:36,251 --> 01:01:40,722
Melinda had a reputation
for being postmodern in bed.

883
01:01:40,811 --> 01:01:46,727
Life is short. That was a sobering discovery
l made when my mother killed herself.

